docs.snippet: BUENOS AIRES, Sept. 20. -- Neutral delegates to the Chaco Peace Conference here have been busy this week in last frantic efforts to devise some means to break the two-month deadlock and so save the conference from complete failure.

headline.main: WAR CLOUDS LOOM AGAIN OVER CHACO; Peace Conference Is Balked by Uncompromising Stand of the Belligerents. DELEGATES SEEK WAY OUT

byline.original: By JOHN W. WHITE.Special Cable to THE NEW YORK TIMES

docs.snippet: Foreign exchanges were under pressure last week with the imminence of open hostilities between Italy and Ethiopia. The Holland guilder was the only exception to the downward trend, and this bill was apparently benefited by the firm position of Queen...
docs.lead_paragraph: Foreign exchanges were under pressure last week with the imminence of open hostilities between Italy and Ethiopia. The Holland guilder was the only exception to the downward trend, and this bill was apparently benefited by the firm position of Queen Wilhelmina against devaluation, or dropping from the gold standard by Holland.
